newsitem.title: AUSTRALIA: SFE wheat still tradeless but prospects bullish.
newsitem.headline: SFE wheat still tradeless but prospects bullish.

text.p: Sydney Futures Exchange (SFE) wheat futures continued tradeless after the Easter break despite bullish indications from the USDA plantings and stocks report.
SFE settlement quotes ended the session virtually steady.
Ed Scamps of Elders Risk Management Pty Ltd said the Australian wheat futures market was likely to remain quiet until the May/June crop season.

USDA overnight figures which showed U.S. wheat acreage for 1977 at 69.187 million acres, less than the 75.639 million acres of 1996 and down in analysts estimates, were supportive for the international wheat market, he said.
Spring wheat plantings could make up for that but also could be delayed by the expected snow melt, he said.
Wheat's bullish outlook was offset to some extent by the higher U.S. soybean plant, he said.
